Perfect! Since you already have a solid **C/C++ background**, Linux knowledge, Docker basics, and you’re learning Java while building a web server, we can make a **2-week focused roadmap** tailored for a **Junior Technical Staff role at Oracle**. The goal is to strengthen **Java skills, databases, algorithms, and system knowledge** while building a small project you can showcase.

---

## **Week 1: Core Java, OOP & Data Structures**

### **Day 1-2: Java Fundamentals & OOP**

* Java syntax, data types, loops, conditionals.
* Classes, objects, constructors, `this` keyword.
* **OOP Concepts:** inheritance, polymorphism, abstraction, encapsulation.
* Exception handling.
* **Hands-on:** Write small programs that implement these concepts (e.g., a `BankAccount` class hierarchy).

**Resources:**

* [Java Tutorials (Oracle)](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/)
* [Java OOP Concepts Explained](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/java-oops-concepts/)

---

### **Day 3-4: Data Structures in Java**

* Arrays, ArrayList, LinkedList, Stack, Queue, HashMap.
* Learn to use Java Collections Framework.
* **Hands-on:** Implement simple algorithms using these structures (e.g., stack-based calculator, phonebook using HashMap).

**Resources:**

* [Java Collections Tutorial](https://www.javatpoint.com/collections-in-java)
* [LeetCode Easy Problems](https://leetcode.com/problemset/all/?difficulty=Easy)

---

### **Day 5-6: Algorithms & Problem-Solving**

* Sorting: bubble, selection, insertion, quicksort basics.
* Searching: linear and binary search.
* Simple recursion problems.
* **Hands-on:** Solve 2–3 problems per day on arrays, strings, and recursion.

**Resources:**

* [HackerRank Java Tutorials](https://www.hackerrank.com/domains/tutorials/10-days-of-java)
* [LeetCode Easy & Medium](https://leetcode.com/problemset/all/)

---

### **Day 7: Java Project Start**

* Start building a **mini web server project** in Java:

  * Handle HTTP GET requests.
  * Serve static files.
  * Log requests to console.
* Integrate **basic OOP principles** in your server code.

---

## **Week 2: Databases, Networking, and Docker Integration**

### **Day 8-9: SQL & Databases**

* Learn **basic SQL**: `SELECT`, `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, `DELETE`.
* Joins, primary keys, foreign keys.
* Optional: Basic **PL/SQL** for Oracle DB.
* **Hands-on:** Connect your Java web server to a local SQLite/MySQL database to store logs or user info.

**Resources:**

* [SQL Tutorial (W3Schools)](https://www.w3schools.com/sql/)
* [Oracle SQL Basics](https://www.oracle.com/database/technologies/sql.html)

---

### **Day 10: Networking & Web Concepts**

* HTTP basics, TCP/IP, sockets in Java.
* URL parsing, request headers, response codes.
* **Hands-on:** Enhance your web server to handle multiple connections using **threads**.

**Resources:**

* [Java Networking Tutorial](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/introduction-to-java-networking/)

---

### **Day 11: Docker & Deployment**

* Containerize your web server using Docker.
* Map ports, mount volumes, and run in a container.
* Optional: Create a simple `docker-compose.yml` if using a database.

**Resources:**

* [Dockerize a Java App](https://docs.docker.com/samples/java/)

---

### **Day 12-13: Mini Project Enhancement**

* Add **logging**, **basic authentication**, or **REST endpoints**.
* Use **Java collections and OOP** effectively.
* Test with **multiple clients** to demonstrate networking understanding.

---

### **Day 14: Final Touch & Preparation**

* Refactor your code, add **comments and README**.
* Prepare a **short presentation or GitHub repo**.
* Review **common interview questions** for junior Oracle engineers:

  * OOP questions.
  * Data structures and algorithms.
  * SQL queries.
  * Basic networking.

**Optional Interview Practice:**

* Solve **2–3 LeetCode Medium problems**.
* Explain your mini web server project, architecture, and Docker integration.

---

✅ **Goal by the End of 2 Weeks:**

* Solid Java fundamentals and OOP knowledge.
* Hands-on mini web server project (with optional database integration).
* Basic algorithms and data structure problem-solving.
* Understanding of networking and Docker deployment.
* Ready to **showcase your skills in interviews**.

